== Title ==

Is "Iranian strikes on Cyprus" an appropriate title for this article? This seems to imply that Iran attacked the country of Cyprus, which is not the case. Yes, the island of Cyprus was attacked, but only the sovereign British military bases, which are not Cypriot territory, but are (internationally) part of the UK. I think "strikes on Akrotiri" or something "strikes on sovereign British base area on Cyprus" would be more appropriate. [[User:Lamoebas|Lamoebas]] ([[User talk:Lamoebas|talk]]) 06:26, 3 March 2026 (UTC)

:Also, the first paragraph says that the strikes are ''believed'' to have come from Iran/Hezbollah. Surely the title should be adjusted until the origin can be confirmed, as currently the title of the page and it's contents are not aligned. [[Special:Contributions/&#126;2026-14237-50|&#126;2026-14237-50]] ([[User talk:&#126;2026-14237-50|talk]]) 14:02, 5 March 2026 (UTC)

